# Project Structure Rules

When creating new features, modules, or files, you MUST follow this directory structure strictly.

## Directory Layout

```text
liu/
├── App/
│   ├── liuApp.swift # Entry point
│   └── DependencyInjection/ # DI Container (e.g., Factory or DependencyContainer)
├── Presentation/
│   ├── Scenes/ # Screens/Modules (e.g., Home, Profile)
│   │   └── [FeatureName]/
│   │       ├── View/ # SwiftUI Views
│   │       └── ViewModel/ # ObservableObjects handling state & logic
│   └── Components/ # Reusable UI Components
├── Domain/ # Business Logic (Platform Independent)
│   ├── Entities/ # Simple data structures
│   ├── UseCases/ # Business logic execution
│   └── Interfaces/ # Protocols for Repositories/Services
├── Data/ # Implementation details
│   ├── Repositories/ # Implementations of Domain Interfaces
│   ├── DataSources/ # API / Local Database Access
│   └── Models/ # Data Transfer Objects (DTOs)
├── Core/ # Shared Utilities & Helpers
│   ├── Extensions/ # Swift Extensions
│   ├── Utils/ # Common helper functions
│   └── Localization/ # Localization Managers & Strings
└── Resources/
    └── Assets.xcassets # Images & Colors
```

## Rules for New Files

1.  **Features**: New features (screens) must go under `Presentation/Scenes/[FeatureName]`.
    - Create `View/` and `ViewModel/` subdirectories.
2.  **Components**: Reusable UI components go in `Presentation/Components`.
3.  **Domain Logic**:
    - Entities in `Domain/Entities`.
    - Use cases in `Domain/UseCases`.
    - Repository protocols in `Domain/Interfaces`.
4.  **Data Layer**:
    - Repository implementations in `Data/Repositories`.
    - DTOs in `Data/Models`.
    - API/DB code in `Data/DataSources`.
5.  **Core**: Shared utilities and extensions go in `Core/`.
